{{Infobox artist | bgcolour = #6495ED | name = 108 | image = 108 biennale venezia 2007.jpg | caption = 108 working in [[Venezia]] | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1978}} | birth_place = [[Alessandria]], Piedmont, Italy | nationality = Italian | field = [[Graffiti]], [[Street Art]] | training = | movement = | works = | patrons = | influenced by = | influenced = | awards = | elected = | website = http://www.108nero.com/ }}
[[File:Tombino 108 Milano.jpg|thumb|right|[[Manhole cover]] painted by 108 in [[Milano]], [[Italy]].]] '''108''' (born 1978) is an [[Italy|Italian]] artist in the field of [[street art]] and [[contemporary art]] from [[Alessandria]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.woostercollective.com/2004/02/checkin_in_with_108.html |title=Checkin' In With 108 |publisher=Wooster Collective |date=2004-02-13 |accessdate=2010-09-08 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5wV29lbzX?url=http://www.woostercollective.com/2004/02/checkin_in_with_108.html |archivedate=2011-02-14 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>
108 has moved from working in traditional [[graffiti]] art to painting large and mysterious figures that invade public spaces.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bevilacqualamasa.it/english/archivio/2007_Altre_1250/pagina.html |title=Bevilacqua La Masa Foundation |publisher=Bevilacqualamasa.it |date=2007-10-09 |accessdate=2010-09-08|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080105181306/http://www.bevilacqualamasa.it/english/archivio/2007_Altre_1250/pagina.html |archivedate = January 5, 2008|deadurl=yes}}</ref> He was the first writer to use numbers instead of letters for his name.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ekosystem.org/0_ITW/108/108_itw.htm |title=interview 108 (prC_Ok) / ABX3000 |publisher=Ekosystem.org |date= |accessdate=2010-09-08|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20071218023657/http://www.ekosystem.org/0_ITW/108/108_itw.htm |archivedate = December 18, 2007|deadurl=yes}}</ref> He started to work when he was a child on the streets of [[Alessandria]], and used different names. His work has appeared on the streets of [[Milan]], [[Paris]], [[London]], [[Berlin]], and [[New York City]]. His first works known by people are enigmatic “blob”-like yellow shapes. It is his firm intention to make visual chaos. His new works are [[labyrinths]], dead trees, non figurative 3D objects and installations, but especially black and gloomy shapes, becoming one of the biggest and influential artists in graffiti abstractism.<ref>[http://www.spazio.org/limited/limited.html limited no art gallery - milan] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081028013409/http://www.spazio.org/limited/limited.html |date=October 28, 2008 }}</ref> In the last years, he took part in a lot of international exhibitions: Nusign 2.4 in [[Paris]],<ref>{{fr icon}} [http://daspblog.canalblog.com/archives/2004/07/15/62321.html dasp | Expo Nusign]</ref> Urban Edge Show in [[Milano]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.woostercollective.com/2005/02/the_urban_edge_show.html |title=The Urban Edge Show |publisher=Wooster Collective |date= |accessdate=2010-09-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100116005804/http://www.woostercollective.com/2005/02/the_urban_edge_show.html |archive-date=2010-01-16 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> Segundo and Tercer Asalto in [[Zaragoza]]<ref>[http://www.enlafrontera.com/asp/programacion_general2.asp?cod=15&menu=1 :: En La Frontera ::] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080129215939/http://www.enlafrontera.com/asp/programacion_general2.asp?cod=15&menu=1 |date=January 29, 2008 }}</ref> and, in 2007 he was invited to join the project called Walls<ref>[http://www.lodominelli.com/2007/06/18/arsenale-venice-walls-larte-al-muro-108-jr-daim/ The Blog has been transferred to WWW.BRIGHTDISORDER.COM » Arsenale / Venice - “Walls l’arte al muro”: 108, JR, Daim] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080828035239/http://www.lodominelli.com/2007/06/18/arsenale-venice-walls-larte-al-muro-108-jr-daim/ |date=August 28, 2008 }}</ref> inside the [[Biennale di Venezia]] with [[JR (artist)|JR]] and Daim. During March 2008 he was invited to join Nomadaz <ref>{{cite web|last=Mauer |first=Mark |url=http://blogs.laweekly.com/lurker/gallery/nomadaz-street-art-from-spain/ |title=Nomadaz: Street Art from Europe at Scion / LA WEEKLY |publisher=Blogs.laweekly.com |date=2008-03-11 |accessdate=2010-09-08|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080401001549/http://blogs.laweekly.com/lurker/gallery/nomadaz-street-art-from-spain/ |archivedate = April 1, 2008|deadurl=yes}}</ref> (a show curated by [[Pablo Aravena]]) in [[Los Angeles]] with [[Eltono]], [[Dem (artist)|Dem]], [[Microbo]] and other artists to represent Europe in the U.S.A. 108’s doomy black abstractions are engaging and challenging in equal measure. Whether it be within the confines of a small room in the abandoned monastery, where the large triangular constructions are most effective and have the effect of warping and playing with the room’s dimensions as the viewer attempts to back away and comprehend the pieces, or as a surreal floating void on a wall beside a busy road.
==Principal exhibits== * 2014 - ''Genius Loci'', Sale d'Arte City of Alessandria, Italy. * 2013 - ''La Tour'', Curated by Galerie Itinerrance, Paris, France. * 2012 - ''Seventeen Dens'', solo show, Ego Gallery, Lugano, Switzerland. * 2011 - ''Fame festival 2010'', Grottaglie, Taranto, Italy. * 2011 - ''La forma dell'inverno'', solo show, curated by Pietro Rivasi, Spazio Avia Pervia, Modena, Italy. * 2010 - ''Agli antipodi della realtà'', Solo show, curated by Guillaume Von Holden, Zelle Arte Contemporanea, Palermo, Italy. * 2010 - ''Sweet Sheets (Moves to Modica)'', Palazzo della Cultura di Modica, Modica, Italy. * 2010 - ''Fame festival 2010'', Grottaglie, Taranto, Italy. * 2009 - ''L'eterno ascoltare delle pietre'', solo show, Studiodieci - Vercelli, Italy. * 2008 - ''Nomadaz'', Los Angeles, USA. * 2007 - ''Walls - [[Venice Biennale]]'', Venezia. * 2006 - ''Segundo Asalto'', Zaragoza, Spain. * 2005 - ''Urban Edge Show'', Milano. * 2004 - ''Nusign 2.4'', Paris. * 2003 - ''Street art show'', Leeds.
